                        <interp inst="t18480612-name-218" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN HYNAM</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a blacking and ink manufacturer, of Prince's-square, Wilson-street, Finsbury. The prisoner was in my employ—the nature of his employment was inserted in a memorandum prior to a bond which he was to give—we sent him a draft of the bond, but he never returned it—I have not got the memorandum—I signed it, and he took it with him—I believe he signed it too—the arrangement was entered into when he began to be employed by me the first time.</p>
